  "prompt": "Why has Akhilesh been expelled from SP by Mulayam?",
  "response": "Mulayam Singh Yadav expelled his son Akhilesh Yadav from the Samajwadi Party (SP) due to internal conflicts and power struggles within the party. The rift between Mulayam Singh Yadav and Akhilesh Yadav became public when Akhilesh, as the Chief Minister of Uttar Pradesh, took steps that clashed with his father's authority and decisions. These disagreements were related to candidate selections, party leadership, and overall control of the party. The expulsion was a result of these escalating tensions, which ultimately led to a major showdown between the father and son within the SP.",
